title: Bug 114470 [Smoke] Error message throws when using new Date('3/2/2005') as value in table filter.
description: When attempting to use the value new Date('3/2/2005') in a table filter, an error message is displayed.
OB: When using new Date('3/2/2005') as the value in a table filter, an error message is thrown.
EB: When using new Date('3/2/2005') as the value in a table filter, no error message should be thrown and the filter should work as expected.
SR:
Steps to reproduce:
1. Open the application with the table filter functionality.
2. Enter the value new Date('3/2/2005') in the filter field.
3. Press Enter or click the Filter button.
4. Observe if an error message is displayed and the filter is not applied correctly.
